{"word":"H441 - אַלּוּף - ʼallûwph - al-loof' - Captain","slug":"H441","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אַלּוּף</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼallûwph"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>al-loof'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Captain"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05DC;&#x05BC;&#x05E3;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D0;&#x05DC;&#x05BC;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05E3; - 'alu&#x0302;ph  'allu&#x0302;ph</b> - <i>al-loof', al-loof'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H502\">H502</a>; <i>familiar</i>; a <i>friend</i>, also <i>gentle</i>; hence a <i>bullock</i> (as being tame; applied, although masculine, to a <i>cow</i>); and so a <i>chieftain</i> (as notable like neat cattle): - captain, duke, (chief) friend, governor, guide, ox."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H503\">H503</a>, <a href=\"#/H505\">H505</a>, <a href=\"#/H507\">H507</a>"}]}